<span class="displaytext"><b>arlington, va -- </b>u.s. senator (candidate full)'s campaign today announced its north carolina sheriffs for (candidate last) leadership. the coalition leadership will work to build on (candidate full)'s grassroots support in their communities. <p>"(candidate full) has made tough choices and always put his country first," said coalition co-chair b.j. barnes, a thirty-four year veteran of law enforcement and current sheriff of guilford county. "as a sheriff and former member of the military, i believe (candidate full) will lead this country with honor, integrity, compassion and strength of character, and it's for those reasons that i will be supporting (candidate full) for president." </p><p>co-chair sheriff steve bizzell of johnston county said, "(candidate full) has always been a staunch advocate for our nation's police force. in the senate (candidate full) supported legislation which ensured law enforcement officials would have the tools they need to protect our nation. senator (candidate last) also sponsored and supported bills designed to win the war on drugs and protect our children from sexual exploitation. (candidate full) has consistently advocated for stricter criminal penalties for repeat felons, gang members and drug dealers. i am proud to support his campaign for the presidency." </p><p>(candidate full) added, "i am grateful for the support of sheriff barnes and bizzell, as well as the other distinguished coalition leaders. i thank each one of them, and the hundreds and thousands of law enforcement officers across america who put their lives on the line every day to keep america safe, for their tremendous sacrifice and commitment to our security." </p><p>today in indianapolis (candidate full) addressed the national sheriffs association. </p><p><b>north carolina sheriffs for (candidate last) leadership</b> </p><p><b>statewide co-chairs<br/></b>sheriff b.j. barnes, guilford county<br/>sheriff steve bizzell, johnston county<br/